article_title: GMO Labeling Faces Ballot Test in Oregon, Colorado
article_text:
Voters in Oregon and Colorado will decide this week whether food makers must label their products as containing genetically modified ingredients, marking a test of consumers’ desire to know more about what they eat.

The most common genetically modified foods are corn, soybeans and sugar beets, which are often engineered to withstand pesticides. They are then processed into ingredients such as high fructose corn syrup or soybean...
